    <name>
				<text>14.2.2.4 Finding r.m.s. of trig functions</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Calculate the r.m.s. value of the following, to 4 decimal places.</p><br>

<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <li>
        <p>\(f(t)={@f1@}\) across \([{@a1@},{@b1@}]\)</p>
        <p>r.m.s. value \(=\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>\(f(t)={@f2@}\) across \([{@a2@},{@b2@}]\)</p>
        <p>r.m.s. value \(=\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p>
    </li>

    <li>
        <p>\(f(t)={@f7@}\) across \([{@a7@},{@b7@}]\)<br><span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">r.m.s. value \(=\) [[input:ans7]] [[validation:ans7]] [[feedback:prt7]]</span></p>
    </li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>Remember the Key Point, r.m.s. value \(\displaystyle = \sqrt{\frac{1}{b-a} \int_a^b [f(t)]^2 \ \mathrm{d}t}\).</p><br>

<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <li>Using the Key Point with \(a={@a1@}\), \(b={@b1@}\) and \(f(t)={@f1@}\) we have: \[\begin{aligned}\text{r.m.s. value }&amp;= \sqrt{\frac{1}{{@b1@}-{@a1@}} \int_{@a1@}^{@b1@} \left[{@f1@}\right]^2 \ \mathrm{d}t}\\ &amp;= \sqrt{{@1/(b1-a1)@}\left[{@integrate(f1^2,t)@}\right]_{@a1@}^{@b1@}}\\
        &amp;= \sqrt{{@1/(b1-a1)@}\left[{@subst(t=b1,integrate(f1^2,t))@}-{@subst(t=a1,integrate(f1^2,t))@}\right]}\\ &amp;\approx {@ta1@} \end{aligned}\]</li>

    <li>Using the Key Point with \(a={@a2@}\), \(b={@b2@}\) and \(f(t)={@f2@}\) we have: \[\begin{aligned}\text{r.m.s. value }&amp;= \sqrt{\frac{1}{{@b2@}-{@a2@}} \int_{@a2@}^{@b2@} \left[{@f2@}\right]^2 \ \mathrm{d}t}\\ &amp;= \sqrt{{@1/(b2-a2)@}\left[{@integrate(f2^2,t)@}\right]_{@a2@}^{@b2@}}\\
        &amp;= \sqrt{{@1/(b2-a2)@}\left[{@subst(t=b2,integrate(f2^2,t))@}-{@subst(t=a2,integrate(f2^2,t))@}\right]}\\ &amp;\approx {@ta2@} \end{aligned}\]</li>



    <li>Using the Key Point with \(a={@a7@}\), \(b={@b7@}\) and \(f(t)={@f7@}\) we have: \[\begin{aligned}\text{r.m.s. value }&amp;= \sqrt{\frac{1}{{@b7@}-{@a7@}} \int_{@a7@}^{@b7@} \left[{@f7@}\right]^2 \ \mathrm{d}t}\\ &amp;= \sqrt{{@1/(b7-a7)@}\left[{@integrate(f7^2,t)@}\right]_{@a7@}^{@b7@}}\\
        &amp;= \sqrt{{@1/(b7-a7)@}\left[{@subst(t=b7,integrate(f7^2,t))@}-\left({@subst(t=a7,integrate(f7^2,t))@}\right)\right]}\\ &amp;\approx {@ta7@} \end{aligned}\]</li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
